<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-27T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="959" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d959">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.34/3–2246: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-27T20:00:00-05:00">March 27, 1946—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>63. Before giving its approval Dept wishes your recommendation on Navy
                            Dept proposal to sell to Paraguay from surplus 18 landing craft of
                            assorted sizes and types armed with small guns and suitable for river
                            transportation of personnel and vehicles. These small vessels requested
                            by Paraguay in staff conversations, and constitute Navy interim program
                            for Paraguay. Similar allocations being made to several other countries
                            including Uruguay, Peru, Ecuador, Chile.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>